                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15515.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-21T18:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Constitutionalist statement is that they were obliged to evacuate in order to
                    prevent raiders from north cutting communication at Ometusco. Not stated why it
                    was necessary to withdraw entire force. Says they will reoccupy within a
                    week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
